# Namma Madras — Cursor Rules

## Stack
- React Native with Expo SDK 54+
- Expo Router (file-based routing — use /app directory)
- TypeScript strict mode throughout (strict: true in tsconfig)
- NativeWind v4 for styling (Tailwind class names in React Native)
- Zustand for global state management
- expo-sqlite (v16+) for all local data access
- expo-localization for device locale detection
- i18next + react-i18next for all UI strings

## Absolute Rules
- NEVER hardcode user-facing strings in components. ALL strings go in /i18n/ta.json and /i18n/en.json.
- NEVER fetch place data from the network in any user-facing component or screen. All place data comes from expo-sqlite only.
- NEVER use AsyncStorage for place data, category data, or emergency contacts. SQLite only (AsyncStorage allowed for small prefs: language, onboarding flags).
- EVERY component that renders place or UI text must accept lang: 'ta' | 'en' prop OR read from Zustand language store.
- Emergency contacts screen must render with ZERO network calls and ZERO async operations beyond SQLite read (sync getAllSync after DB is ready).

## File Structure
/app              — Expo Router routes (tabs, detail screens, onboarding)
/components       — Shared UI components (PlaceCard, StatusChip, etc.)
/db               — expo-sqlite helpers, queries, migrations
/stores           — Zustand stores (language, persona, savedPlaces, location)
/i18n             — Translation files: ta.json, en.json
/data             — seed SQL fragments (seedSQL.ts)
/assets           — fonts via @expo-google-fonts

## Data Access Pattern
- db/queries.ts — all SQLite access; components call query functions, never raw SQL in JSX.

## Styling
- Use NativeWind classes everywhere.
- Minimum tap target: min-h-[48px] min-w-[48px] on interactive controls where practical.
- Dark-first UI per PRD.

## Prohibited Patterns
- No class components
- No direct SQL strings in components (use /db/queries.ts)
- No network calls in user-facing place flows
- No emoji in UI (use icon components)
